{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":146,"text":"I'll never forget that day"},{"time":1824,"text":"back in the spring of 2006."},{"time":5723,"text":"I was a surgical resident"},{"time":7302,"text":"at The Johns Hopkins Hospital,"},{"time":9733,"text":"taking emergency call."},{"time":11510,"text":"I got paged by the E.R. around 2 in the morning"},{"time":14873,"text":"to come and see a woman with a diabetic ulcer"},{"time":16900,"text":"on her foot."},{"time":18694,"text":"I can still remember sort of that smell of rotting flesh"},{"time":22395,"text":"as I pulled the curtain back to see her."},{"time":26022,"text":"And everybody there agreed this woman was very sick"},{"time":28367,"text":"and she needed to be in the hospital."},{"time":29719,"text":"That wasn't being asked."},{"time":31319,"text":"The question that was being asked of me was a different one,"},{"time":33461,"text":"which was, did she also need an amputation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":37390,"text":"Now, looking back on that night,"},{"time":40357,"text":"I'd love so desperately to believe that I treated that woman"},{"time":45522,"text":"on that night with the same empathy and compassion"},{"time":48658,"text":"I'd shown the 27-year-old newlywed"},{"time":52893,"text":"who came to the E.R. three nights earlier"},{"time":54838,"text":"with lower back pain"},{"time":56452,"text":"that turned out to be advanced pancreatic cancer."},{"time":60701,"text":"In her case, I knew there was nothing I could do"},{"time":62864,"text":"that was actually going to save her life."},{"time":64632,"text":"The cancer was too advanced."},{"time":66681,"text":"But I was committed to making sure that"},{"time":69361,"text":"I could do anything possible to make her stay"},{"time":71784,"text":"more comfortable. I brought her a warm blanket"},{"time":74207,"text":"and a cup of a coffee."},{"time":76927,"text":"I brought some for her parents."},{"time":79112,"text":"But more importantly, see, I passed no judgment on her,"},{"time":82258,"text":"because obviously she had done nothing"},{"time":84155,"text":"to bring this on herself."},{"time":86329,"text":"So why was it that, just a few nights later,"},{"time":89142,"text":"as I stood in that same E.R. and determined"},{"time":92300,"text":"that my diabetic patient did indeed need an amputation,"},{"time":95711,"text":"why did I hold her in such bitter contempt?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99615,"text":"You see, unlike the woman the night before,"},{"time":102080,"text":"this woman had type 2 diabetes."},{"time":104479,"text":"She was fat."},{"time":106031,"text":"And we all know that's from eating too much"},{"time":107944,"text":"and not exercising enough, right?"},{"time":110299,"text":"I mean, how hard can it be?"},{"time":112983,"text":"As I looked down at her in the bed, I thought to myself,"},{"time":115344,"text":"if you just tried caring even a little bit,"},{"time":118232,"text":"you wouldn't be in this situation at this moment"},{"time":121222,"text":"with some doctor you've never met"},{"time":122999,"text":"about to amputate your foot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126814,"text":"Why did I feel justified in judging her?"},{"time":130456,"text":"I'd like to say I don't know."},{"time":133025,"text":"But I actually do."},{"time":135061,"text":"You see, in the hubris of my youth,"},{"time":137392,"text":"I thought I had her all figured out."},{"time":140496,"text":"She ate too much. She got unlucky."},{"time":142326,"text":"She got diabetes. Case closed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145695,"text":"Ironically, at that time in my life,"},{"time":147098,"text":"I was also doing cancer research,"},{"time":149496,"text":"immune-based therapies for melanoma, to be specific,"},{"time":151839,"text":"and in that world I was actually taught to question everything,"},{"time":155812,"text":"to challenge all assumptions"},{"time":157848,"text":"and hold them to the highest possible scientific standards."},{"time":161658,"text":"Yet when it came to a disease like diabetes"},{"time":165034,"text":"that kills Americans eight times more frequently than melanoma,"},{"time":168583,"text":"I never once questioned the conventional wisdom."},{"time":172011,"text":"I actually just assumed the pathologic sequence of events"},{"time":175057,"text":"was settled science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177642,"text":"Three years later, I found out how wrong I was."},{"time":181042,"text":"But this time, I was the patient."},{"time":183642,"text":"Despite exercising three or four hours every single day,"},{"time":187473,"text":"and following the food pyramid to the letter,"},{"time":190038,"text":"I'd gained a lot of weight and developed something"},{"time":192195,"text":"called metabolic syndrome."},{"time":194480,"text":"Some of you may have heard of this."},{"time":196464,"text":"I had become insulin-resistant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199909,"text":"You can think of insulin as this master hormone"},{"time":202358,"text":"that controls what our body does with the foods we eat,"},{"time":206421,"text":"whether we burn it or store it."},{"time":208535,"text":"This is called fuel partitioning in the lingo."},{"time":211349,"text":"Now failure to produce enough insulin is incompatible with life."},{"time":214525,"text":"And insulin resistance, as its name suggests,"},{"time":217181,"text":"is when your cells get increasingly resistant"},{"time":219861,"text":"to the effect of insulin trying to do its job."},{"time":223374,"text":"Once you're insulin-resistant,"},{"time":225550,"text":"you're on your way to getting diabetes,"},{"time":226925,"text":"which is what happens when your pancreas"},{"time":228989,"text":"can't keep up with the resistance and make enough insulin."},{"time":232312,"text":"Now your blood sugar levels start to rise,"},{"time":234940,"text":"and an entire cascade of pathologic events"},{"time":237572,"text":"sort of spirals out of control that can lead to heart disease,"},{"time":241273,"text":"cancer, even Alzheimer's disease,"},{"time":244882,"text":"and amputations, just like that woman a few years earlier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249764,"text":"With that scare, I got busy changing my diet radically,"},{"time":252725,"text":"adding and subtracting things most of you would find"},{"time":254902,"text":"almost assuredly shocking."},{"time":257982,"text":"I did this and lost 40 pounds, weirdly while exercising less."},{"time":261861,"text":"I, as you can see, I guess I'm not overweight anymore."},{"time":264902,"text":"More importantly, I don't have insulin resistance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267069,"text":"But most important, I was left"},{"time":269113,"text":"with these three burning questions that wouldn't go away:"},{"time":272962,"text":"How did this happen to me if I was supposedly"},{"time":275411,"text":"doing everything right?"},{"time":278108,"text":"If the conventional wisdom about nutrition had failed me,"},{"time":281143,"text":"was it possible it was failing someone else?"},{"time":284930,"text":"And underlying these questions,"},{"time":286830,"text":"I became almost maniacally obsessed"},{"time":290076,"text":"in trying to understand the real relationship"},{"time":292803,"text":"between obesity and insulin resistance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296433,"text":"Now, most researchers believe obesity"},{"time":299249,"text":"is the cause of insulin resistance."},{"time":302641,"text":"Logically, then, if you want to treat insulin resistance,"},{"time":304756,"text":"you get people to lose weight, right?"},{"time":306648,"text":"You treat the obesity."},{"time":309412,"text":"But what if we have it backwards?"},{"time":312118,"text":"What if obesity isn't the cause of insulin resistance at all?"},{"time":315489,"text":"In fact, what if it's a symptom of a much deeper problem,"},{"time":319409,"text":"the tip of a proverbial iceberg?"},{"time":322231,"text":"I know it sounds crazy because we're obviously in the midst"},{"time":324874,"text":"of an obesity epidemic, but hear me out."},{"time":328093,"text":"What if obesity is a coping mechanism"},{"time":331307,"text":"for a far more sinister problem going on"},{"time":334909,"text":"underneath the cell?"},{"time":336391,"text":"I'm not suggesting that obesity is benign,"},{"time":338757,"text":"but what I am suggesting is it may be the lesser"},{"time":341060,"text":"of two metabolic evils."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343771,"text":"You can think of insulin resistance as the reduced capacity"},{"time":346790,"text":"of our cells to partition fuel,"},{"time":348777,"text":"as I alluded to a moment ago,"},{"time":351068,"text":"taking those calories that we take in"},{"time":352990,"text":"and burning some appropriately and storing some appropriately."},{"time":356429,"text":"When we become insulin-resistant,"},{"time":358071,"text":"the homeostasis in that balance deviates from this state."},{"time":361438,"text":"So now, when insulin says to a cell,"},{"time":363566,"text":"I want you to burn more energy"},{"time":365611,"text":"than the cell considers safe, the cell, in effect, says,"},{"time":368046,"text":"\"No thanks, I'd actually rather store this energy.\""},{"time":372478,"text":"And because fat cells are actually missing most of"},{"time":374380,"text":"the complex cellular machinery found in other cells,"},{"time":377182,"text":"it's probably the safest place to store it."},{"time":379953,"text":"So for many of us, about 75 million Americans,"},{"time":384922,"text":"the appropriate response to insulin resistance"},{"time":388537,"text":"may actually be to store it as fat, not the reverse,"},{"time":393466,"text":"getting insulin resistance in response to getting fat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398810,"text":"This is a really subtle distinction,"},{"time":400985,"text":"but the implication could be profound."},{"time":404352,"text":"Consider the following analogy:"},{"time":406850,"text":"Think of the bruise you get on your shin"},{"time":409819,"text":"when you inadvertently bang your leg into the coffee table."},{"time":413411,"text":"Sure, the bruise hurts like hell, and you almost certainly"},{"time":416298,"text":"don't like the discolored look, but we all know"},{"time":419279,"text":"the bruise per Se is not the problem."},{"time":422732,"text":"In fact, it's the opposite. It's a healthy response to the trauma,"},{"time":426474,"text":"all of those immune cells rushing to the site of the injury"},{"time":429235,"text":"to salvage cellular debris and prevent the spread"},{"time":432219,"text":"of infection to elsewhere in the body."},{"time":434917,"text":"Now, imagine we thought bruises were the problem,"},{"time":438639,"text":"and we evolved a giant medical establishment"},{"time":441507,"text":"and a culture around treating bruises:"},{"time":444647,"text":"masking creams, painkillers, you name it,"},{"time":447930,"text":"all the while ignoring the fact that people"},{"time":450156,"text":"are still banging their shins into coffee tables."},{"time":453776,"text":"How much better would we be if we treated the cause --"},{"time":456979,"text":"telling people to pay attention"},{"time":458544,"text":"when they walk through the living room --"},{"time":460147,"text":"rather than the effect?"},{"time":463420,"text":"Getting the cause and the effect right"},{"time":465297,"text":"makes all the difference in the world."},{"time":467776,"text":"Getting it wrong, and the pharmaceutical industry"},{"time":470855,"text":"can still do very well for its shareholders"},{"time":473535,"text":"but nothing improves for the people with bruised shins."},{"time":477451,"text":"Cause and effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480295,"text":"So what I'm suggesting is"},{"time":482132,"text":"maybe we have the cause and effect wrong"},{"time":484889,"text":"on obesity and insulin resistance."},{"time":487523,"text":"Maybe we should be asking ourselves,"},{"time":489300,"text":"is it possible that insulin resistance causes weight gain"},{"time":493185,"text":"and the diseases associated with obesity,"},{"time":495251,"text":"at least in most people?"},{"time":496781,"text":"What if being obese is just a metabolic response"},{"time":499781,"text":"to something much more threatening,"},{"time":502002,"text":"an underlying epidemic,"},{"time":504213,"text":"the one we ought to be worried about?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":506770,"text":"Let's look at some suggestive facts."},{"time":508242,"text":"We know that 30 million obese Americans"},{"time":510728,"text":"in the United States don't have insulin resistance."},{"time":513701,"text":"And by the way, they don't appear to be at any"},{"time":515638,"text":"greater risk of disease than lean people."},{"time":518718,"text":"Conversely, we know that six million lean people"},{"time":521602,"text":"in the United States are insulin-resistant,"},{"time":525039,"text":"and by the way, they appear to be at even greater risk"},{"time":528106,"text":"for those metabolic diseases I mentioned a moment ago"},{"time":530261,"text":"than their obese counterparts."},{"time":532083,"text":"Now I don't know why, but it might be because,"},{"time":534320,"text":"in their case, their cells haven't actually figured out"},{"time":537010,"text":"the right thing to do with that excess energy."},{"time":540295,"text":"So if you can be obese and not have insulin resistance,"},{"time":543614,"text":"and you can be lean and have it,"},{"time":545485,"text":"this suggests that obesity may just be a proxy"},{"time":549918,"text":"for what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552942,"text":"So what if we're fighting the wrong war,"},{"time":555357,"text":"fighting obesity rather than insulin resistance?"},{"time":559157,"text":"Even worse, what if blaming the obese"},{"time":562400,"text":"means we're blaming the victims?"},{"time":565125,"text":"What if some of our fundamental ideas about obesity"},{"time":568844,"text":"are just wrong?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570702,"text":"Personally, I can't afford the luxury of arrogance anymore,"},{"time":574825,"text":"let alone the luxury of certainty."},{"time":577408,"text":"I have my own ideas about what could be at the heart of this,"},{"time":580254,"text":"but I'm wide open to others."},{"time":582166,"text":"Now, my hypothesis, because everybody always asks me,"},{"time":584885,"text":"is this."},{"time":586502,"text":"If you ask yourself, what's a cell trying to protect itself from"},{"time":589631,"text":"when it becomes insulin resistant,"},{"time":591358,"text":"the answer probably isn't too much food."},{"time":594033,"text":"It's more likely too much glucose: blood sugar."},{"time":597683,"text":"Now, we know that refined grains and starches"},{"time":599977,"text":"elevate your blood sugar in the short run,"},{"time":602033,"text":"and there's even reason to believe that sugar"},{"time":603941,"text":"may lead to insulin resistance directly."},{"time":606742,"text":"So if you put these physiological processes to work,"},{"time":610837,"text":"I'd hypothesize that it might be our increased intake"},{"time":614310,"text":"of refined grains, sugars and starches that's driving"},{"time":617173,"text":"this epidemic of obesity and diabetes,"},{"time":621824,"text":"but through insulin resistance,"},{"time":623662,"text":"you see, and not necessarily through just overeating and under-exercising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627574,"text":"When I lost my 40 pounds a few years ago,"},{"time":630159,"text":"I did it simply by restricting those things,"},{"time":632759,"text":"which admittedly suggests I have a bias"},{"time":636215,"text":"based on my personal experience."},{"time":638576,"text":"But that doesn't mean my bias is wrong,"},{"time":641231,"text":"and most important, all of this can be tested scientifically."},{"time":645184,"text":"But step one is accepting the possibility"},{"time":648291,"text":"that our current beliefs about obesity,"},{"time":650663,"text":"diabetes and insulin resistance could be wrong"},{"time":653669,"text":"and therefore must be tested."},{"time":656544,"text":"I'm betting my career on this."},{"time":658935,"text":"Today, I devote all of my time to working on this problem,"},{"time":663060,"text":"and I'll go wherever the science takes me."},{"time":666233,"text":"I've decided that what I can't and won't do anymore"},{"time":669764,"text":"is pretend I have the answers when I don't."},{"time":672808,"text":"I've been humbled enough by all I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676916,"text":"For the past year, I've been fortunate enough"},{"time":679073,"text":"to work on this problem with the most amazing team"},{"time":682486,"text":"of diabetes and obesity researchers in the country,"},{"time":685890,"text":"and the best part is,"},{"time":687195,"text":"just like Abraham Lincoln surrounded himself with a team of rivals,"},{"time":691094,"text":"we've done the same thing."},{"time":692590,"text":"We've recruited a team of scientific rivals,"},{"time":695853,"text":"the best and brightest who all have different hypotheses"},{"time":699298,"text":"for what's at the heart of this epidemic."},{"time":700912,"text":"Some think it's too many calories consumed."},{"time":703293,"text":"Others think it's too much dietary fat."},{"time":705672,"text":"Others think it's too many refined grains and starches."},{"time":709142,"text":"But this team of multi-disciplinary,"},{"time":711750,"text":"highly skeptical and exceedingly talented researchers"},{"time":714734,"text":"do agree on two things."},{"time":717022,"text":"First, this problem is just simply too important"},{"time":720671,"text":"to continue ignoring because we think we know the answer."},{"time":723414,"text":"And two, if we're willing to be wrong,"},{"time":726198,"text":"if we're willing to challenge the conventional wisdom"},{"time":728735,"text":"with the best experiments science can offer,"},{"time":731798,"text":"we can solve this problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734103,"text":"I know it's tempting to want an answer right now,"},{"time":737158,"text":"some form of action or policy, some dietary prescription --"},{"time":741655,"text":"eat this, not that —"},{"time":743384,"text":"but if we want to get it right,"},{"time":745064,"text":"we're going to have to do much more rigorous science"},{"time":747298,"text":"before we can write that prescription."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750151,"text":"Briefly, to address this, our research program"},{"time":752750,"text":"is focused around three meta-themes, or questions."},{"time":755993,"text":"First, how do the various foods we consume"},{"time":758888,"text":"impact our metabolism, hormones and enzymes,"},{"time":761689,"text":"and through what nuanced molecular mechanisms?"},{"time":764507,"text":"Second, based on these insights,"},{"time":766757,"text":"can people make the necessary changes in their diets"},{"time":769716,"text":"in a way that's safe and practical to implement?"},{"time":773447,"text":"And finally, once we identify what safe"},{"time":776456,"text":"and practical changes people can make to their diet,"},{"time":779484,"text":"how can we move their behavior in that direction"},{"time":783159,"text":"so that it becomes more the default"},{"time":785412,"text":"rather than the exception?"},{"time":787268,"text":"Just because you know what to do doesn't mean"},{"time":789688,"text":"you're always going to do it."},{"time":791197,"text":"Sometimes we have to put cues around people"},{"time":793325,"text":"to make it easier, and believe it or not,"},{"time":795628,"text":"that can be studied scientifically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799269,"text":"I don't know how this journey is going to end,"},{"time":801853,"text":"but this much seems clear to me, at least:"},{"time":806066,"text":"We can't keep blaming our overweight and diabetic patients"},{"time":811062,"text":"like I did."},{"time":813974,"text":"Most of them actually want to do the right thing,"},{"time":816253,"text":"but they have to know what that is,"},{"time":819622,"text":"and it's got to work."},{"time":822668,"text":"I dream of a day when our patients can"},{"time":827364,"text":"shed their excess pounds"},{"time":829099,"text":"and cure themselves of insulin resistance,"},{"time":831912,"text":"because as medical professionals,"},{"time":834642,"text":"we've shed our excess mental baggage"},{"time":836612,"text":"and cured ourselves of new idea resistance sufficiently"},{"time":839938,"text":"to go back to our original ideals:"},{"time":843028,"text":"open minds, the courage to throw out yesterday's ideas"},{"time":847445,"text":"when they don't appear to be working,"},{"time":850773,"text":"and the understanding that scientific truth isn't final,"},{"time":853892,"text":"but constantly evolving."},{"time":856640,"text":"Staying true to that path will be better for our patients"},{"time":859932,"text":"and better for science."},{"time":863180,"text":"If obesity is nothing more than a proxy"},{"time":866174,"text":"for metabolic illness,"},{"time":868100,"text":"what good does it do us to punish those with the proxy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":873397,"text":"Sometimes I think back to that night in the E.R."},{"time":877941,"text":"seven years ago."},{"time":880254,"text":"I wish I could speak with that woman again."},{"time":883878,"text":"I'd like to tell her how sorry I am."},{"time":887133,"text":"I'd say, as a doctor, I delivered"},{"time":890020,"text":"the best clinical care I could,"},{"time":893680,"text":"but as a human being,"},{"time":897577,"text":"I let you down."},{"time":899985,"text":"You didn't need my judgment and my contempt."},{"time":904230,"text":"You needed my empathy and compassion,"},{"time":908728,"text":"and above all else, you needed a doctor"},{"time":910723,"text":"who was willing to consider"},{"time":913352,"text":"maybe you didn't let the system down."},{"time":916416,"text":"Maybe the system, of which I was a part,"},{"time":919634,"text":"was letting you down."},{"time":922073,"text":"If you're watching this now,"},{"time":924874,"text":"I hope you can forgive me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929112,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}